          Over 400 years ago, the last king was slain, signalling the   
          end of an era when angels walked among mortals and men        
          ruled from a palace. The lands fell to disorder and           
          lawlessness. Great cities crumbled. Believing the Angelkind   
          have abandoned them, the people fled to smaller               
          settlements, banding together to survive the chaos.           
                                                                        
          Now bandits stalk the roads and wild animals infest the       
          fields. The only safety can be found in fortified, isolated   
          villages. In the struggle for survival, relations between     
          the different sentient races have always been fragile. At     
          times, mistrust and conflict have even erupted into           
          full-blown wars.                                              
                                                                        
          Striving to keep the people together is the Holy Order of     
          Atonement, but even their influence is limited to a handful   
          of settlements. And to top it all off, many believe the       
          legend of a "Vindicator" who would someday walk the land as   
          a punisher of all sins and unleash a swift end upon the world.
                                                                        
          That day has come.                                            
          
         
